    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Irregular granular pattern embossed on bookcloth in imitation of leather. "Morocco" refers to a type of goatskin leather. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047530/Publishers' Bindings Online (2005)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Motivo granulado de forro de libro, "marroquí" se refiere a un tipo de piel de odre (cabra). Modelo de granulado irregular grabado en relieve sobre forro de libro en imitación al cuero marroquí.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
